        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I would keep them.  There are various uses of them later on from putting them towards Research, Evocation, or Abjuration  if you don't practice them enough.  This gives you the flexibility, later on, to use them in bunches, or get yourself over a difficult skill hump.  I needed a bunch for Evocation and Abjuration when I was in my mid 40's because we got 2 very important spells that used these skills and I didn't keep them up to snuff througout my career.  I never fought a lot of undead (Evocation for undead DD) and almost never used my own shielding spells (Abjuration).  So, I dumped a boat load of points (and PP) into these skills to raise them very quickly as well as casting my lowest lvl of these types of spells during downtime to greatly reduce my fizzles.  For example, I could expend a whole bar of mana just trying to get Dead Man Floating (Abjuration) to cast once.</P><P>Wurtin</P><P>54th lvl Heretic of E'ci<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
